âœ… Disable / Enable Summary
âœ… Disable

When you click the heart:

You add the item id to the isDisabled array:

setIsDisabled(prev => [...prev, items.id]);


React re-renders the component.

The heart checks:

isDisabled.includes(items.id)


If true â†’ it adds:

pointer-events-none opacity-50


âž¡ So the heart becomes unclickable and looks disabled.

âœ… Enable

When you remove the item:

You remove the item id from isDisabled:

setIsDisabled(prev => prev.filter(id => id !== itemId));


React re-renders.

isDisabled.includes(items.id) becomes false.

Heart becomes clickable again.

ðŸ”‘ Key Idea

âœ” isDisabled is a list of disabled item IDs
âœ” If ID exists â†’ disabled
âœ” If ID removed â†’ enabled